column21: Note: This paper separated 'low shrubs' and 'tall shrubs'. I used the data for 'low shrubs'
Also, this paper separated out all variables into 'natives' and 'exotics'. I added the two together when necessary.

There were three degrees of severety for 'burn': 0 = no burn, 1 = low severity, and 2 = high severity. I used low severity for the burn data.
Only has data for immediately after treatments and 5 years later. I am using the 5 years later data.
There is only data for shrubs, but I am going to include this paper in the total.richness file. In doing so I am assuming that shrubs serve as an indicator species for other understory species.
